        "body": "Description\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes the issue where @shikijs/rehype would replace the original <pre> element and drop any data or properties added earlier in the remark/rehype pipeline (e.g., metadata from code fences like fileName=\"hello.js\" or line-highlight instructions).\r\n\r\nThe solution introduces optional data and properties fields to CodeToHastOptions, forwards the original node’s metadata from the rehype plugin, and merges it into the final syntax-highlighted <pre> element. This keeps Shiki’s output intact while preserving important metadata for downstream plugins.\r\n\r\nLinked Issues\r\n\r\nFixes #629\r\n\r\nAdditional context\r\n\r\nIncoming properties are merged first; Shiki’s critical properties intentionally override when necessary.\r\n\r\nBackward-compatible: no changes required for existing Shiki users.",
